    feat(postfx): add CRT phosphor burn-in / persistence effect
    
    New postfx pass 'crt-burn-in' maintains a ring buffer (16 frames) of
    recent snapshots and composites fading ghosts under the current frame.
    
    Key design decisions:
    - History is thread-local (not cleared on scene transition) so the old
      scene's content fades out naturally under the new one — real CRT feel.
    - Exponential decay curve: ghost_weight = intensity × decay^age
    - Ghost blends weakly through bright content, strongly through dark areas.
    - Captures every 3rd frame to keep memory low (~16 snapshots).
    - Parameterised via standard effect params:
        intensity (ghost strength), alpha (max blend), speed (decay rate),
        brightness (ghost luminance multiplier).
    
    Added to all 5 CRT-TEST playground screens via fx.mrmo.burn preset.
    
