Author: Pawel Potepa <pawel.potepa@hotmail.com>
Date:   Sat Mar 21 20:05:03 2026 +0100

    perf: optimize prerender hot path — eliminate sort allocations
    
    Three optimizations in the OBJ render pipeline:
    
    1. face_avg_depth(): replace Vec collect() with inline sum/count loop
       — eliminates ~20-30K heap allocations per render call in the sort
       comparator (called 1440× during prerender)
    
    2. Pre-compute depth keys before sort: compute face_avg_depth() once
       per face, store alongside face ref, sort by pre-computed key.
       Old: O(N log N) calls to face_avg_depth inside comparator.
       New: O(N) calls + O(N log N) float comparisons.
    
    3. Share source strings via Arc<str> across rayon work items to avoid
       1440 String allocations during parallel prerender.
    
